==English==

===Pronunciation===
*[[IPA]]: /ɑɹ̰ː(ː)/ (♪: <sub>╰—</sub> )

===Interjection===
'''argh!'''
# {{internet}} {{slang}}: An utterance used to express dismay, embarassment or frustration.

===Usage note===
''Arrggh!'', ''Aaaarrrggghhh!!!'' or any repeating series of a, r, g, h, and !, in sequence, conveys the same meaning<!--; all are considered incorrect and/or illiterate nonsense--><!--The post-semicolonic clause is conspicuously POV.—Ed.>.

